review_blob: Mild hops and a subtle bitter finish makes it clean and drinkable. Moderate carbonation off the tap also lifted it above other IPAs. Slight caramel flavours with hints of white fruits.
beer_name: Monkey Monk Reaktor Hello World API IPA

review_blob: The roasted malts and strong carbonation makes this a rich but light drop. A good depth of flavour without being over powerful. Burnt caramel hits first then some subtle hops - dark fruits mostly. Well worth a try

A big head that youd expect from a saison. Carbonation is low so too head resilience. Very yeasty on the nose and eyes (much sediment). A good flavour but not as crisp or as tangy as I expected. There are many farmie qualities to it - straw, grass, yeast - its almost more stable than farm house. Stronger than it tastes.

Drinkable at the very least. A clean ale that makes up for a lack of complexity with its crystal amber appearance. Mild hoppiness makes it much more of a session beer than its step brother Pale Ale. Drink very cold on a boat
A personal favorite session beer. Cloudy and vibrant on tap or from a bottle. A good level of bitterness. Hard to find outside Australia but becoming more popular in Europe now

Its like a baby bear cub - a fluffy brown mass thats almost threatening. Chocholet and rye dominate its unique mmmi like taste. The head is thin but resilient giving a surprisingly smooth texture. Its strength (7,3%) is evedent in its sweetness. Worth a try but Id like to meet mamma bear

the sweet aroma and bitter finish give it a more-ish quality. A clear, light appearance makes me think of summer sessions in the sun. Unfortunately the thin head takes away from the crispness and leave it all a bit flat.
